{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>Here is a simple model of a politician in Haskell, which you can use to create arbitrary politician instances.\nYou only need to provide that particular politician's body of knowledge and its individual mapping between a statement and a corresponding fallacy. The answering is already implemented.</p>\n<p><div id=\"gist6273665\" class=\"gist\">\n    <div class=\"gist-file\">\n      <div class=\"gist-data\">\n        <div class=\"js-gist-file-update-container js-task-list-container file-box\">\n  <div id=\"file-politician-hs\" class=\"file\">\n    \n\n  <div itemprop=\"text\" class=\"blob-wrapper data type-haskell \">\n      \n<table class=\"highlight tab-size js-file-line-container\" data-tab-size=\"8\">\n      <tr>\n        <td id=\"file-politician-hs-L1\" class=\"blob-num js-line-number\" data-line-number=\"1\"></td>\n        <td id=\"file-politician-hs-LC1\" class=\"blob-code blob-code-inner js-file-line\"><span class=\"pl-k\">module</span> <span class=\"pl-c1\">Politics</span> <span class=\"pl-k\">where</span></td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td id=\"file-politician-hs-L2\" class=\"blob-num js-line-number\" data-line-number=\"2\"></td>\n        <td id=\"file-politician-hs-LC2\" class=\"blob-code blob-code-inner js-file-line\">\n</td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td id=\"file-politician-hs-L3\" class=\"blob-num js-line-number\" data-line-number=\"3\"></td>\n        <td id=\"file-politician-hs-LC3\" class=\"blob-code blob-code-inner js-file-line\">  <span class=\"pl-k\">import</span> <span class=\"pl-c1\">Data.List</span></td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td id=\"file-politician-hs-L4\" class=\"blob-num js-line-number\" data-line-number=\"4\"></td>\n        <td id=\"file-politician-hs-LC4\" class=\"blob-code blob-code-inner js-file-line\">\n</td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td id=\"file-politician-hs-L5\" class=\"blob-num js-line-number\" data-line-number=\"5\"></td>\n        <td id=\"file-politician-h